wiki.text:
'Modi' can refer to:

* Monochorionic-Diamniotic, a type of twin
* Modi (surname), a surname used in India
* Móði, one of Thor's sons
* Modi Rosenfeld, stand up comedian
* Modi script, a historical script used in the Maratha empire
* Murugappa Channaveerappa Modi, Indian eye surgeon
* Minoan Modi, the site of a Minoan peak sanctuary in eastern Crete
* Narendra Modi, chief minister of Gujarat
* Emperor Modi (disambiguation), several Chinese Emperors' name
* Lalit Modi, cricket administrator, Commissioner of Indian Premier League
* Modi, Chania, a village in western Crete
* Modi Group, India-based conglomerate
* Microsoft Office Document Imaging, (MODI) such as for the 2003 Object Model
* Modi Khola, a tributary of the Gandaki River in Nepal, draining south from the
  Annapurna Himalaya
